Introduction to Pandas
pandas is a fast, powerful, flexible and easy to use open source data analysis and manipulation tool,
built on top of the Python programming language.

Pandas vs Python
Python – A general-purpose programming language used for everything — web apps, AI, automation, and more.

Pandas – A powerful data analysis library built on Python, made for handling, cleaning, and analyzing data easily.

Key Differences:

Nature:

Python → All-rounder language
Pandas → Data expert inside Python

Purpose:
Python → Builds any type of program
Pandas → Makes data handling fast & simple

Data Structures:
Python → Lists, Dictionaries, Tuples
Pandas → DataFrame (table-like), Series (1D labeled data)

Functionality:
Python → Needs extra libraries for analysis
Pandas → Built-in tools for cleaning, merging, and analyzing data

In short:
Python is the base. Pandas is the power tool that makes data work easy, fast, and fun! 
